  --- Why c3, c5, c7 have Delta = 0 ---
    c_3: Re(z^3) has D^{2r} for r=0,...,1, max D power = 2
      Max D power 2 < 8, so no S8 (or higher) dependence
      Since Delta(S4)=0, Delta(S6)=0: Delta(c_3)=0
    c_5: Re(z^5) has D^{2r} for r=0,...,2, max D power = 4
      Max D power 4 < 8, so no S8 (or higher) dependence
      Since Delta(S4)=0, Delta(S6)=0: Delta(c_5)=0
    c_7: Re(z^7) has D^{2r} for r=0,...,3, max D power = 6
      Max D power 6 < 8, so no S8 (or higher) dependence
      Since Delta(S4)=0, Delta(S6)=0: Delta(c_7)=0

  --- S10 CANCELLATION at p=11 ---
  At p=11, m=5, H = f(S4,S6,S8) exactly (S10 not needed)
  This means: sum_{k odd} (2/k) * coeff_S10_in_Re(z^k) = 0
  when summed with appropriate alpha_j weights

  S_10 coefficient in alpha_1 = sum c_k for p=11:
    c_11: (2/11)*C(11,10)*(-1/2)^1*(-1)^5 = 1.00000000
    Total S10 coeff in alpha_1 = 1.00000000 = 1

